{
  "stem": "19218.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 308.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They immediately gathered us to a place and demanding things which they knew were impossible, like they need 100 pounds of pepper, 100 pounds of cocoa.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Those are spices, I mean, which didn't even grow in-- in Poland, and they had to deliver it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, everybody emptied out whatever they had and, of course, to bring all the gold and silver and everything else.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it didn't take long, and [BACKGROUND NOISE] we were evacuated from our town, Hajnowka, to a ghetto, Pruzana, which was closer to the Russian border, the part of Poland that we lived during the Russian occupation, which was the same town, but it was called White Russia, which is today, I guess, White Russia, or Belarus they call it.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Now, the evacuation-- the evacuation of-- of the city, just take whatever you can, so how much can you carry on you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we-- we were marched for about five kilometers into the highway, which was in the forest on both sides.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "During that little march, they managed to kill our, well, our rabbi, whose name-- I do not remember the first name.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I have a document somewheres, which I couldn't put my hands on now.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "His name was Kopf, K-O-P-F, Kopf.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He was a very strong man.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And during that march, they-- the rabbi had to carry the physician on his back, was a Jewish physician.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they had the-- the rabbi dig a grave.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And what I witnessed is, they took a shovel, the shovel which the rabbi was digging the grave, and they just chopped off the skull of the doctor and killed him right there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And then they shot the rabbi, and they-- and of course, we burn him.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
